    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>'Long Goodbye,' Yes</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gene D Phillips letter agrees with David Thomson's assertion in June 11 article that The Long Goodbye is one of Robert Altman's best films (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Orchids to David Thomson for focusing on ''The Long Goodbye'' as one of Robert Altman's ''astonishing'' films of the 70's. It is the most underrated and neglected of all of the movies based on the crime fiction of Raymond Chandler.</p>
        <p>GENE D. PHILLIPS  Chicago</p>
      </block>
